  "content": "# editor components should be modular with separate files\n\nWhen building document editors:\n\n- Create modular components for UI elements in separate files for maintainability\n- Separate business logic (dispatch, data transformation) from presentation (rendering, layout)\n- Use TypeScript strictly \u2014 avoid `any` and type casting\n- Consider components from `@powerhousedao/design-system` and `@powerhousedao/document-engineering`\n\nThis modularity makes editors easier to test, maintain, and update when the underlying document model evolves.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[editor patterns]]",
